    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-20T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-20T16:00:00-05:00" n="328"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 (D) Regulations/2399: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-20T15:00:00-06:00"
                            >May 20, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 21—4:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>220. Reference to Department’s telegram no. 218, May 10, 7 p.m. Mexican
                    Government generally agrees to contents of Department’s telegram no. 218 and my
                    note no. 5146 of May 12 to the Foreign Office.<note n="40" xml:id="d328fn40"
                        >Latter not printed.</note> Note from Foreign Office of May 19 indicates
                    desire of Mexican Government to apply export control not only to products <pb
                        facs="0415" n="407" xml:id="pg_407"/> mentioned in Department’s telegram no.
                    218 but to all products on the United States export control list which are
                    produced in Mexico. Note from the Foreign Office states that Mexico is selecting
                    its representative and is only awaiting the arrival in Mexico City of the
                    representative of the United States to begin conversations. Spanish text and
                    translation of note are being sent by air mail today.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Daniels</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
